WEBVTT

00:07:28.778 --> 00:07:31.612
to deliver his stem-winders,

00:07:31.636 --> 00:07:33.315
he was doing that from memory.

00:07:33.339 --> 00:07:37.117
If you want to memorize a speech,

00:07:37.141 --> 00:07:40.847
don't try and memorize it word for word,

00:07:40.871 --> 00:07:43.069
because that's going to make
you sound robotic,

00:07:43.093 --> 00:07:44.991
you're going to forget the next word --

00:07:45.015 --> 00:07:47.738
that's not a good way
to speak persuasively.

00:07:48.046 --> 00:07:51.724
What you should do is create an image

00:07:51.748 --> 00:07:55.550
of each of the topics that you want
to talk about in your speech,

00:07:55.574 --> 00:07:59.938
put the images of those topics
into a memory palace.